The Kynge was at the Wyndowes, and with hym the Erle of Surrey, and many others, Prelatts and Lordes. All doon, the Kynge went to hys Sou'pper, and with hym the said Erle of Surrey, and many others. The Qene was in lyk wys at the Wyndowes of hyr Lodgyng, acompayned of the Ladyes of the Countre, and others of hyr Company.

After Soupper, the Kynge and the Qene being togeder in hyr grett Chamber, John Inglish and hys Companyons playd, and then ichon went his Way.

’ That Day Syre Richard Poulle, Syr Davy Owen, John Huse, Syre Edward Stanneley, and many others, tuke theyr Conge of the King, and of the Qene, and went theyr Way. ,
